<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/5878365-marilyn"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_100x100-6433b08cbe793211f55e184d39e84c4d.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/5878365-marilyn">Marilyn</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">NO. This is a cozy mystery at best. Agatha Christie novels are for people who like serious mysteries they have to ponder about for the length of the b<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">NO. This is a cozy mystery at best. Agatha Christie novels are for people who like serious mysteries they have to ponder about for the length of the book. I can't imagine boy crush in a Christie novel. A cozy mystery is a " I don't want to have to think but, I want to be entertained by light reading" And, every reader been there.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
