<span id="freeTextContainer13088632715434336433"><i>Percy wrote: &quot;YES!!! I’m reading this book right now and I’m 100% in agreement. I lived in Charleston for 7 years and the racial history of the city i</i></span>
  <span id="freeText13088632715434336433" style="display:none"><i>Percy wrote: "YES!!! I’m reading this book right now and I’m 100% in agreement. I lived in Charleston for 7 years and the racial history of the city is so important and so often erased. This book’s whitewashed a..."</i><br /><br />Hello, I'm finally checking in on this account, and while I've never been to Charleston I know enough about South Carolina to be aware that there are Black people there. Also, WHOA, that description of Timothy Neville must be in the first book (which I still haven't read), I am now thinking of tracking down a copy and revising my review to excoriate this. I may have been far too kind to the series, back in 2009.</span>
